eraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23186.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dont know if Capt Rottgrime is charmable or not- but,</span><hr size=1> sarnaks in OT do NOT give VS faction. they give + legion of cabilis faction, - brood of dizok, - sarnak collective. there is no mention of VS anywhere when killing sarnaks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujaguarjp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jaguarjp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/7/02 1:31:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23186.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> OK, OK.. next idea...</span><hr size=1> Well, we all by now should have an idea about how &quot;Aggro ticks&quot; work... So, with that in mind, I'd like to present MY half-baked, non-guaranteed idea:<br>
<br>
Have a Bard group with you, and stroll in while said Bard plays his Invisibility song. You will see the song messages(turn them ON), &quot;A cloud of mist surrounds you&quot; or something to that effect, as they pulse. That's the easy part, heres where it gets tricky- time the pulses so that JUST before you are about to recieve another pulse, hand in a braid. With a little luck(and only IF my theory applies here) you will get the pulse of the invis song just AFTER the trade window gets opened, BUT, if timed right with the aggro ticks, BEFORE he aggros on you.<br>
<br>
OOH! just had another idea, you could even use it along with the above idea:<br>
<br>
Have a non-KOS buddy turn in 3 braids. Then, you could turn in the 4th braid, and click the &quot;Trade&quot; button real fast, and even if he turns around and starts beating on you, I think the trade should complete. And, since you are the one turning in the final Braid, you will complete the cycle. And, since you will be grouped with a Bard, just haul ass, you don't even hafta die. *NOTE* Please attempt this stuff at NIGHT, when General is out on Walkabout, to increase your chances of actually surviving the experience...<br>
<br>
